  <!-- ── Under the hood ── -->
  <section class="ibr-section">
    <h2 class="ibr-section-title">Under the hood</h2>
    <div class="ibr-tech-grid">
      <div class="ibr-tech-card">
        <h3>SQL Server temporal tables</h3>
        <p>Every page row is system-versioned. Any prior state — including which widget versions it
        referenced — is recoverable. Wiki-like history with no separate history table.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ibr-tech-card">
        <h3>Entity Framework Core</h3>
        <p>No raw SQL in application code. Bridge tables everywhere — one row per fact, no JSON
        blobs for structured data. Migrations are additive and never destructive.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ibr-tech-card">
        <h3>Collectible Assembly Load Contexts</h3>
        <p>Each widget DLL loads in its own ALC, isolated from the host. Replacing a widget
        unloads the old DLL and loads the new one. The host process never restarts.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ibr-tech-card">
        <h3>Single Blazor circuit per page</h3>
        <p>One interactive circuit. Every widget on a page shares it. No per-widget SignalR
        connection, no per-widget app pool. Interactive where needed, static where not.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ibr-tech-card">
        <h3>Content trust model</h3>
        <p>Inline JavaScript only executes when the author holds the
        <code class="ibr-code-inline">Cms.AuthorRawMarkup</code> claim. Untrusted HTML is
        sanitized at render time. Trust is stamped at write time, not read time.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="ibr-tech-card">
        <h3>Admin inbox</h3>
        <p>Every missing, disabled, or misconfigured widget surfaces a deduplicated alert in
        the admin inbox — the page degrades gracefully and the problem is never silent.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Get started ── -->
  <section class="ibr-section ibr-section--cta">
    <h2 class="ibr-section-title">Get started in four steps</h2>
    <div class="ibr-steps-grid">
      <div class="ibr-step">
        <div class="ibr-step-n">1</div>
        <div>
          <strong>Create a page</strong>
          <p>Admin → Pages → New Page. Set a slug and a title.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="ibr-step">
        <div class="ibr-step-n">2</div>
        <div>
          <strong>Add a widget token</strong>
          <p>Type <code class="ibr-code-inline">{{ MindAttic.Ideas.Component.TabBoard }}</code> into the body editor.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="ibr-step">
        <div class="ibr-step-n">3</div>
        <div>
          <strong>Upload the widget</strong>
          <p>Admin → Upload → drop <code class="ibr-code-inline">MindAttic.Ideas.Component.TabBoard.V1.idea</code>.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="ibr-step">
        <div class="ibr-step-n">4</div>
        <div>
          <strong>Navigate to the page</strong>
          <p>The widget resolves on the next request. No restart. No cache clear. No config change.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <footer class="ibr-footer">
    <p>MindAttic.Ideas &nbsp;·&nbsp; Built on .NET 10 &nbsp;·&nbsp; &copy; <span class="ibr-year">2026</span> Ryan DeBraal</p>
